                            <comment id="14231895" author="stack" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2014 18:43:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;lgtm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Does it work?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14232121" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2014 21:03:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still trying to figure out how to call HConnectionImplementation#getKeepAliveZooKeeperWatcher() in ruby&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14232157" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2014 21:25:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;HConnectionImplementation#getKeepAliveZooKeeperWatcher() is package private.&lt;br/&gt;
HBaseAdmin#getConnection() returns HConnection, not HConnectionImplementation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can getKeepAliveZooKeeperWatcher() be exposed in Connection interface ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do you think, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stack&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stack&quot;&gt;stack&lt;/a&gt; ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14232166" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2014 21:30:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Calling @admin.getConnection().getKeepAliveZooKeeperWatcher() in admin.rb gave me:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
hbase(main):001:0&amp;gt; update_master_config
2014-12-02 13:27:28,829 WARN  [main] util.NativeCodeLoader: Unable to load &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;native&lt;/span&gt;-hadoop library &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; your platform... using builtin-java classes where applicable

ERROR: undefined method `getKeepAliveZooKeeperWatcher&apos; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; #&amp;lt;#&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Class&lt;/span&gt;:0x70265461&amp;gt;:0x319149be&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14232170" author="stack" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2014 21:32:37 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Still trying to figure out how to call HConnectionImplementation#getKeepAliveZooKeeperWatcher() in ruby&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cast the connection as a ClusterConnection then do getMaster and on the returned stub, call getServerName?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suggest avoid directly referencing zk if possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14232174" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2014 21:36:10 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cast the connection as a ClusterConnection&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I searched ClusterConnection among ruby files - no occurrence.&lt;br/&gt;
BTW I looked at some Q&amp;amp;A on casting in ruby - ruby doesn&apos;t seem to support casting.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Digging more.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14232223" author="stack" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2014 22:09:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ClusterConnection is a java interface  May not need to cast at all (Charles Nutter: &quot;You should not have to cast anything in Ruby, since we just dispatch to whatever methods are actually there. If the method is there, you can call it. &quot;)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14232231" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2014 22:22:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;From ClusterConnection :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  MasterService.BlockingInterface getMaster() &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Looking into MasterService.BlockingInterface, I don&apos;t find method which returns ServerName.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14232251" author="stack" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2014 22:41:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My mistake. I looked at wrong Interface. Indeed it is not there.  There seems to be a &apos;hole&apos; in that there is not a means of getting current master other than via private internal class (your v1) which we should not be using out here in client code I&apos;d say.  Maybe we could add a method on Admin.  This issue alone is not argument enough to provide one though I&apos;d argue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14232254" author="stack" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2014 22:42:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marked this as minor (unless you have a real use case that needs this &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ted_yu&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ted_yu&quot;&gt;Ted Yu&lt;/a&gt;).  Can use current shell commands, right?, to do this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
